&gt; Firebase dynamic links are hosted on the customisable subdomain look
&gt; something like https://abcde.page.link where .page.link is subdomain.
&gt; Firebase creates a mini website at this subdomain to host the links.
&gt; Also on that mini website it automatically generates assetlinks.json
&gt; to map dynamic links to your app.
&gt; 
&gt; a) Add your project to firebase
&gt; 
&gt; b) For dynamic links add both SHA-1 and SHA-256 fingerprint
&gt; 
&gt; c) Add dynamic links dependency 

    implementation &#39;com.google.firebase:firebase-dynamic-links:17.0.0&#39;

&gt; d)Go to firebase console -&gt; select project -&gt; select dynamic link menu
&gt; -&gt; Get started: Add the subdomain you want to use for eg: https://abcde.page.link. If you dont want to use page.link subdomain
&gt; you can also use your own. Enter domain www.myapp.page.link and your
&gt; subdomain is ready to go

e) Make sure your app is properly configured.

&gt; To check use: the_name_you_chose.page.link/.well-known/assetlinks.json
&gt; provides configuration details of your project.
&gt; 
&gt; **2) Create a firebase dynamic link**
&gt; 
&gt; a)Create new dynamic link will getting prepopulated short
&gt; link/path(customizable)
&gt; 
&gt; b)Set up dynamic link same as short url.
